::KitKat::

She looked at Gabriel. She wasn't sure how to get all the predacon 
groups together to finish out her council.  There were 6 seats on the 
council.  That was the required number to have on a beginning council 
per the old laws.  She had two seats filled out. She had herself and 
Aracnia.  That left four. She thought about havng Megatron and 
HellBeast on the council. That left two seats open. She wasn't sure 
who would fill them, but she figured the matrix would help her on 
that. 

She then refocused on Gabriel.  "What happens to the others. Tell me, 
what do you know about my future. You said I am to destroy the 
Allience. But what happens to the rest of the groups.  What happens 
to the maximals? To my group?  What happens to my pack, to Drillbit. 
Please tell me? I have to know." her voice showed great concern for 
her group and Drillbit.  She looked at the hologram. "Let our paths 
lead where they may? I have that as a philosiphy, but as a battle 
cry?" She smiled.  "I would have thought that I'd have said something 
like, Predacons unite now and forever, or something like that."
She smiled. She couldn't fight the prophecy. Or at least, she didn't 
think that she could.
